{"colspan":71,"rowspan":71,"colwidth":139,"backgroundColor":139},[7998],{"type":112,"attrs":7999,"content":8000},{"textAlign":139},[8001],{"text":8002,"type":75,"marks":8003},"18 - 24 Month Payback",[8004],{"type":149,"attrs":8005},{"color":2499},{"type":2446,"attrs":8007,"content":8008},{"colspan":71,"rowspan":71,"colwidth":139,"backgroundColor":139},[8009],{"type":112,"attrs":8010,"content":8011},{"textAlign":139},[8012],{"text":8013,"type":75,"marks":8014},"4x+ ROI (Accelerated)",[8015],{"type":149,"attrs":8016},{"color":2499},{"type":69,"attrs":8018,"content":8019},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[8020],{"text":8021,"type":75,"marks":8022},"Human + Agent: Redefining Logistics Roles",[8023,8025],{"type":149,"attrs":8024},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":8027,"content":8028},{"textAlign":139},[8029],{"text":8030,"type":75,"marks":8031},"Terminal’s mission isn't to replace humans but to redeploy them to higher-value tasks. By automating the repetitive \"mission-critical\" data capture at the gate and in the yard, Terminal allows yard masters to focus on strategy and exception handling. This hybrid approach solves the logistics labor gap by making complex yard management accessible to new hires in hours, not weeks.",[8032],{"type":149,"attrs":8033},{"color":3568},{"type":69,"attrs":8035,"content":8036},{"level":1919,"textAlign":139},[8037],{"text":8038,"type":75,"marks":8039},"FAQ: Automating Logistics Workflows with Computer Vision",[8040,8042],{"type":149,"attrs":8041},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":8044,"content":8045},{"textAlign":139},[8046,8052],{"text":8047,"type":75,"marks":8048},"Q: How does Terminal Industries differ from a general computer vision platform like Cogniac or Roboflow? A: General platforms offer \"vision tools\" that you must build yourself. ",[8049,8051],{"type":149,"attrs":8050},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"text":8053,"type":75,"marks":8054},"Terminal provides a full-stack Yard Operating System. We don't just \"see\" a truck; we know its appointment time, its dock priority, and we autonomously dispatch the spotter to move it.",[8055],{"type":149,"attrs":8056},{"color":3568},{"type":112,"attrs":8058,"content":8059},{"textAlign":139},[8060,8066],{"text":8061,"type":75,"marks":8062},"Q: Is the 99% accuracy rate affected by weather or dirty license plates? A: No. Terminal's AI is specifically trained on \"dirty data\"—weather occlusions, glare, and handwritten numbers. ",[8063,8065],{"type":149,"attrs":8064},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"text":8067,"type":75,"marks":8068},"In the Ryder pilot, the system maintained its 99% accuracy despite the real-world scenarios that typically cause traditional OCR systems to fail.",[8069],{"type":149,"attrs":8070},{"color":3568},{"type":112,"attrs":8072,"content":8073},{"textAlign":139},[8074,8080],{"text":8075,"type":75,"marks":8076},"Q: What is the \"Connective Tissue\" benefit of an AI-native YOS™? A: Terminal acts as a unified data hub that \"plays nice\" with your existing WMS, TMS, and ERP. ",[8077,8079],{"type":149,"attrs":8078},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"text":8081,"type":75,"marks":8082},"It bridges the technology gap, feeding 99.5% accurate yard data into your systems so the warehouse never has to wait for the yard.",[8083],{"type":149,"attrs":8084},{"color":3568},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[1882],"The ultimate test of any AI logistics platform is its performance in the \"chaos of the real world.\" In a landmark pilot with Ryder System, Inc., Terminal Industries proved that computer vision could replace manual logs at scale. Across 10,000+ truck detections, the system maintained a 99% accuracy rate for license plates and Department of Transportation (DOT) numbers. This milestone demonstrates that AI-native automation can eliminate the 20-30% of operational time typically lost to manual verification errors and paper-based check-ins.\n",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":8089},{},{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":8091},{},[],"See how Terminal Industries and Ryder achieved 99% accuracy in yard operations. Explore the key lessons from their pilot and what it means for your supply chain.",{"value":1891,"plugin":1892},"the-99-accuracy-benchmark-lessons-from-the-terminal-ryder-pilot","all-resources/the-99-accuracy-benchmark-lessons-from-the-terminal-ryder-pilot",-1430,[],"72451774-11e3-43ce-a6e4-3f8f8b4a5421","2025-12-18T00:00:00.000Z",[],{"name":8103,"created_at":8104,"published_at":8105,"updated_at":8106,"id":8107,"uuid":8108,"content":8109,"slug":8235,"full_slug":8236,"sort_by_date":139,"position":8237,"tag_list":8238,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":1897,"meta_data":139,"group_id":8239,"first_published_at":8240,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":8241,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"The Rise of the Yard Operating System (YOS™): Why Legacy YMS is No Longer Enough","2026-02-02T23:53:13.242Z","2026-02-02T23:54:12.518Z","2026-02-02T23:54:12.530Z",140848305154932,"4e5d53ad-8021-4efa-8672-5abf0ed09261",{"_uid":8110,"body":8111,"link":8227,"title":8103,"author":8228,"excerpt":8229,"category":1232,"subtitle":18,"component":1883,"seo_image":8230,"seo_title":18,"button_text":132,"cover_image":8232,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":18,"background_color":8234},"92273df0-380d-4bb5-8f1b-46fa04479847",{"type":66,"content":8112},[8113,8126,8135,8143,8210,8219],{"type":112,"attrs":8114,"content":8115},{"textAlign":139},[8116,8121],{"text":3564,"type":75,"marks":8117},[8118,8120],{"type":149,"attrs":8119},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"text":8122,"type":75,"marks":8123},"In 2026, the industry is shifting from traditional Yard Management Systems (YMS) to Yard Operating Systems (YOS™). While a YMS acts as a digital ledger for manual entries, an AI-native YOS™ like Terminal Industries uses Computer Vision and Agentic AI to autonomously orchestrate yard activity. This \"Self-Operating Yard\" model delivers a 99% detection accuracy and can increase throughput by over 50% by eliminating the manual \"clipboard and radio\" bottlenecks that plague legacy platforms.",[8124],{"type":149,"attrs":8125},{"color":3568},{"type":69,"attrs":8127,"content":8128},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[8129],{"text":8130,"type":75,"marks":8131},"AI-Native vs. Legacy YMS: The Architectural Divide",[8132,8134],{"type":149,"attrs":8133},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":8136,"content":8137},{"textAlign":139},[8138],{"text":8139,"type":75,"marks":8140},"The primary bottleneck in digitizing the yard is often the software itself. Most platforms available today were built on \"Legacy Architectures\" that require human input to trigger actions.",[8141],{"type":149,"attrs":8142},{"color":3568},{"type":1312,"content":8144},[8145,8161],{"type":1315,"content":8146},[8147],{"type":112,"attrs":8148,"content":8149},{"textAlign":139},[8150,8156],{"text":8151,"type":75,"marks":8152},"Legacy YMS (System of Record): ",[8153,8155],{"type":149,"attrs":8154},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"text":8157,"type":75,"marks":8158},"Relies on guards, drivers, and spotters to manually update statuses. If a human forgets to scan a tag, the system becomes a \"digital fiction.\"",[8159],{"type":149,"attrs":8160},{"color":3568},{"type":1315,"content":8162},[8163],{"type":112,"attrs":8164,"content":8165},{"textAlign":139},[8166,8172,8177,8183,8188,8194,8199,8205],{"text":8167,"type":75,"marks":8168},"Terminal YOS™ (System of Execution): ",[8169,8171],{"type":149,"attrs":8170},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"text":8173,"type":75,"marks":8174},"Designed \"AI-first.\" It uses Agentic AI to perceive reality through camera feeds. If a truck arrives, the system ",[8175],{"type":149,"attrs":8176},{"color":3568},{"text":8178,"type":75,"marks":8179},"sees",[8180,8182],{"type":149,"attrs":8181},{"color":3568},{"type":3690},{"text":8184,"type":75,"marks":8185}," it, ",[8186],{"type":149,"attrs":8187},{"color":3568},{"text":8189,"type":75,"marks":8190},"indexes",[8191,8193],{"type":149,"attrs":8192},{"color":3568},{"type":3690},{"text":8195,"type":75,"marks":8196}," it, and ",[8197],{"type":149,"attrs":8198},{"color":3568},{"text":8200,"type":75,"marks":8201},"assigns",[8202,8204],{"type":149,"attrs":8203},{"color":3568},{"type":3690},{"text":8206,"type":75,"marks":8207}," a dock door autonomously based on real-time warehouse priority.",[8208],{"type":149,"attrs":8209},{"color":3568},{"type":69,"attrs":8211,"content":8212},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[8213],{"text":8214,"type":75,"marks":8215},"Category Creation: The \"Highway to Warehouse\" Bridge",[8216,8218],{"type":149,"attrs":8217},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":8220,"content":8221},{"textAlign":139},[8222],{"text":8223,"type":75,"marks":8224},"Terminal Industries is recognized in the 2025 Gartner Market Guide for Yard Management as a category creator. We don't just \"manage\" the yard; we bridge the technology chasm between transportation (TMS) and warehousing (WMS). By integrating these systems, the YOS™ ensures that the yard is a strategic nerve center, not a black hole of detention fees.",[8225],{"type":149,"attrs":8226},{"color":3568},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[1882],"In 2026, the industry is shifting from traditional Yard Management Systems (YMS) to Yard Operating Systems (YOS™). While a YMS acts as a digital ledger for manual entries, an AI-native YOS™ like Terminal Industries uses Computer Vision and Agentic AI to autonomously orchestrate yard activity. This \"Self-Operating Yard\" model delivers a 99% detection accuracy and can increase throughput by over 50% by eliminating the manual \"clipboard and radio\" bottlenecks that plague legacy platforms.\n",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":8231},{},{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":8233},{},{"value":1891,"plugin":1892},"the-rise-of-the-yard-operating-system-yostm-why-legacy-yms-is-no-longer-enough","all-resources/the-rise-of-the-yard-operating-system-yostm-why-legacy-yms-is-no-longer-enough",-1310,[],"4853adf4-c919-460d-a606-1e7ed3df68a4","2025-12-16T00:00:00.000Z",[],{"name":8243,"created_at":8244,"published_at":8245,"updated_at":8246,"id":8247,"uuid":8248,"content":8249,"slug":8604,"full_slug":8605,"sort_by_date":139,"position":8606,"tag_list":8607,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":1897,"meta_data":139,"group_id":8608,"first_published_at":8609,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":8610,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"From Gate to Dock: Building Autonomous Yard Workflows with Agentic AI","2026-02-02T23:54:26.433Z","2026-02-02T23:55:46.957Z","2026-02-02T23:55:46.973Z",140848604945272,"b0132920-1492-41ee-b807-2f9f4cd4de99",{"_uid":8250,"body":8251,"link":8596,"title":8243,"author":8597,"excerpt":8598,"category":1232,"subtitle":18,"component":1883,"seo_image":8599,"seo_title":18,"button_text":132,"cover_image":8601,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":18,"background_color":8603},"c2ccbd2f-7826-4445-996d-699eea69af00",{"type":66,"content":8252},[8253,8266,8275,8283,8292,8300,8309,8317,8326,8334,8539,8554,8568,8582],{"type":112,"attrs":8254,"content":8255},{"textAlign":139},[8256,8261],{"text":3564,"type":75,"marks":8257},[8258,8260],{"type":149,"attrs":8259},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"text":8262,"type":75,"marks":8263},"Autonomous yard workflows are no longer theoretical. By combining Computer Vision and Agentic AI, Terminal Industries has successfully automated the gate-to-dock journey. In a landmark pilot with Ryder, Terminal achieved 99% accuracy in capturing license plates and DOT numbers across 10,000+ detections. This automation allows for Gate Acceleration™, reducing check-in times by 85% and enabling a seamless, agent-led transition for every asset entering the facility.",[8264],{"type":149,"attrs":8265},{"color":3568},{"type":69,"attrs":8267,"content":8268},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[8269],{"text":8270,"type":75,"marks":8271},"How Agentic AI Orchestrates the Yard",[8272,8274],{"type":149,"attrs":8273},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":8276,"content":8277},{"textAlign":139},[8278],{"text":8279,"type":75,"marks":8280},"\"Agentic AI\" refers to systems that can assess an operational state, formulate a plan, and execute tasks autonomously.",[8281],{"type":149,"attrs":8282},{"color":3568},{"type":69,"attrs":8284,"content":8285},{"level":1919,"textAlign":139},[8286],{"text":8287,"type":75,"marks":8288},"Step 1: Automated Gate Intelligence",[8289,8291],{"type":149,"attrs":8290},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":8293,"content":8294},{"textAlign":139},[8295],{"text":8296,"type":75,"marks":8297},"Using Terminal-in-a-Camera™, the system identifies moving vehicles as they enter. It reconciles the vehicle profile against the TMS appointment and provides the driver with a dynamic parking assignment—all in under 2 minutes.",[8298],{"type":149,"attrs":8299},{"color":3568},{"type":69,"attrs":8301,"content":8302},{"level":1919,"textAlign":139},[8303],{"text":8304,"type":75,"marks":8305},"Step 2: Intelligent Tasking & Spotter Dispatch",[8306,8308],{"type":149,"attrs":8307},{"color":3568},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":8310,"content":8311},{"textAlign":139},[8312],{"text":8313,"type":75,"marks":8314},"Instead of a dispatcher manually assigning moves, the Agentic AI monitors dock availability. When a door opens, it automatically \"missions\" the nearest spotter to move the highest-priority trailer. This \"Intelligent Mission Control\" reduces asset search time by 90%.",[8315],{"type":149,"attrs":8316},{"color":3568},{"type":69,"attrs":8318,"content":8319},{"level":1919,"textAlig